                    <h3>Betting Rules</h3>
                    <h2>General Rules</h2>
                    <p>The customer declares upon the settlement of bets:<br/>
                    1.	That you have read and understand the company’s terms and conditions.<br/>
                    2.	That you have been sufficiently informed as to the betting rules for all types of bets and is aware of the betting and payout limits and accepts all these.<br/>
                    3.	That the funds with which you place bets do not stem from any unlawful action and that you freely disposes over such.<br/>
                    4.	That you are aware of the danger of addiction to gaming with respect to betting, and that you have not applied to be barred from gambling or betting with other private or state-run companies.</p>
                    <p>The betting agreement shall come about through the acceptance of a betting offer. For a bet to be valid, the bet needs to be checked and confirmed by the customer. Upon confirmation, the customer will receive a confirmation message if the bet has been settled successfully. The bet may be viewed in the pending bets panel, bet list or in the customer’s statement.</p>
                    <p>Any unilateral right to withdrawal from the agreement on the part of the customer (cancellation of bets) following the conclusion of the Agreement is excluded. The customer may correct or cancel the bet selection before the final confirmation of the settlement of the bet. Upon the confirmation, the customer shall be obligated to fulfill the agreement.</p>
                    <p>The company has no obligation to list additional information such as the type of competition, racing distances, etc. If additional information is nevertheless provided, this shall be without engagement and shall not have any influence on the settlement of the bets. The same shall apply to all types of statistics, tables and other data.</p>
                    <p>The company shall be entitled to void respective bets (including retroactively) if there is a suspicion of manipulation or betting fraud. In legal terms this shall mean that the stake monies in the bets in question shall be credited to the betting account and the customer shall be barred from future betting, remaining funds in the account shall be paid out.</p>
                    <p>Settlement of bets shall be performed after announcement of official ranking. In case there has been any objection or disqualification in respect to the race result, the company will follow all directives given by the race organizer.</p>
                    <p>When a bet is being accepted, the time (MU Time) when it was approved is shown in your bet list and also on your statement. However if any race or event start officially before acceptance of your bet, it will not be accepted.</p>
                    <p>All odds displayed on the website are shown in decimal of "100", which would be for example in the case of betting 100 unit currency on winning-odd 200 will result a payout of 200 unit currency.</p>
                    <h2>Horse Withdrawals</h2>
                    <p>Any withdrawal of a horse before the first trumpet (Normal Withdrawal) in respect of any particular race will entail the cancellation and a refund of all bets placed on the horses in respect of that race. </p>
                    <p>In the event the client accepts that the company replaces bets subject to horse withdrawals, bets not including withdrawn horse will be replaced on new odds and race status for that particular race. Otherwise the bet will be refunded to the client’s account.</p>
                    <p>Apart from Single Win bets, all other bet types and combinations will be replaced automatically after the withdrawal of a horse. In case the bet selection includes the withdrawn horse, the company will remove the withdrawn horse from the bet while replacing the bet. </p>
                    <p>Any withdrawal of a horse after the first trumpet (Withdrawal on Pitch) will entail a refund of all bets placed on the withdrawn horse and a percentage deduction on the winning amounts in accordance with the scale of deduction established by the race organizer.</p>
                    <p>In case of withdrawal of all horses except one, betting on that race will be canceled and all bets refunded.</p>
                    <h2>Dead Heat</h2>
                    <p>Where a dead heat is declared by the horse racing organizer, the winning punter will have his winning amount divided by the number of horses finishing dead heat. In case of dead heat in a two horse race, betting will be canceled and all bets refunded.</p>
                    <h2>Bet Types</h2>
                    <p>The following types of bets are being offered by the company. We have the right to add new games or discontinue others at our own discretion. The betting customer is not entitled to claim any type of bet which is not available.</p>
                    <p><b>Win</b>&nbsp;- A bet that will give a return if the selection finishes first in the event.</p>
                    <p><b>Win Accumulators</b>&nbsp;- All the selections chosen must pass the finish line first to give a return.</p>
                    <p><b>Place</b>&nbsp;- A bet that will give a return if:<br/>
                        &nbsp;&nbsp;(i) For 8 runners or more, the selection finishes first or second or third.<br/>
                    &nbsp;(ii) For 5 – 7 runners, the selection finishes first or second.<br/>
                    (iii) For races having less than 5 runners, place is not offered.</p>
                    <p><b>Place Accumulators</b>&nbsp;- All the selections chosen must pass the finish line first, second or third to give a return. Place condition applies.<br/>
                     <h2>Settlement of Bets</h2>
                    <p>A bet is considered to have been won if the placing was valid and was won according to the selected type of bet as per the rules already mentioned.</p>
                    <p>All winnings will automatically be credited to your betting account to the maximum payout. The company reserves the right to withhold credit to the customer's account until an official race report has been published.</p>
